The Adamawa State government has set aside N2 billion to end incidence of malaria in the state by 2020. Speaking on the occasion of the 2018 World Malaria Day yesterday, the Commissioner of Health, Dr Fatima Atiku Abubakar, said through the permanent secretary, Kennedy Bantimawus, that the government had procured and distributed 2.5 million treated mosquito nets in 2017 to prevent residents from infection. In his remark, the Program Manager of the Malaria Elimination Program, Isaac Kadala called on residents to take advantage of the testing kits and drugs supplied by the state government by visiting health centres to know their status before receiving medication.